  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of the present protocol is to prove if the observed actions (AOb) will improve the
      cervical range of motion (CROM) in patients with non-specific chronic neck pain (CNP). This
      study is a parallel-group double blind randomized clinical. Outcome measures were CROM, and
      pressure pain detection thresholds (PPDT) with a digital algometer. The follow-up will
      consist of three evaluations: pre- treatment, post-treatment and 10 minutes after second
      measurement (motor imagery).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
